    <h1>Compilation</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman &middot; 1996 &middot; <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-35.html#%_sec_5.5">SICP &sect;5.5</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A compiler translates Scheme to register machine code ahead of time. The compiled code is faster because decisions made at compile time don&rsquo;t repeat at runtime. The compiler itself is a Scheme program.</p>
    </div>

